<%= render PageWrappers::GuestComponent.new do %>
  <section class="mx-auto my-12">
    <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
    <h2 class="mt-4">1.1. Account Master Data</h2>
    <p>An account is required to use the features of our products. If you decide to create an account, you can authenticate by using different providers, like Github or Gitlab. In this case, we will use the information of such a service, including your email address, for authentication on our service. You can also create and use multiple accounts.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-4">1.2. Collected information</h2>
    <p class="mb-2">Service can collect next information:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your account's email</li>
      <li>Pull request's (PR) author, creation time, merging time, changed Lines of Code</li>
      <li>PR comment's author, creation time</li>
      <li>PR review's author, creation time, status</li>
      <li>Author's email, account icon</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Pull requests information can be collected only after providing Personal Access Token with read-only access to specific repositories that you have access.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-4">1.3. Private messaging and private communication</h2>
    <p>Service does not provide the ability to communicate between users through the service.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-4">2.1. Location Information</h2>
    <p>The service does not collect or store information about your location.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-4">2.2. Cookies</h2>
    <p>A cookie is a small data file that is stored on your computer or mobile device. Like many websites, we use cookies and similar technologies to manage our services. Cookies are required to save authentication data when connecting through a Github or Gitlab server.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-4">3.1. Separation of control</h2>
    <p>We do not disclose your personal data.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-4">4.1. Access or reduction of your personal data</h2>
    <p>If you have registered an account with PullKeeper, application only stores email provided by another services that you use for authentication. You can change such information at another services that you use.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-4">4.2. Delete</h2>
    <p>If you want to delete an account, then you can do it from profile page.</p>
  </section>
<% end %>
